1. *Period* je važan za žensko zdravlje. (The *period* is important for women's health.)
2. Moj profesor engleskog jezika daje dosta zadataka u kratkom *periodu* vremena. (My English teacher gives a lot of homework in a short *period* of time.)
3. Moja sestra uči uči o istoriji u *periodu* renesanse. (My sister is studying history in the *period* of the Renaissance.)
4. U školi sam naučila da se tačka stavlja na kraj rečenice, a *period* na kraj pasusa. (In school, I learned that a period goes at the end of a paragraph, and a *period* at the end of a sentence.)
5. *Periodični* sistem elemenata je osnova za proučavanje hemije. (The periodic table of elements is the foundation for studying chemistry.)
6. Početak 20. veka smatra se *periodom* velikih društvenih promena. (The beginning of the 20th century is considered a *period* of significant social changes.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "period" can be used in various forms, such as "period", "perioda", "periodu", "periodom", "periodični", etc.